item.title: Cant change? --Need Help--
item.dc:creator: @bob2568 bob2568
item.description:
@bob2568 wrote:

This is not a text. It is an interface. Let me assist you, open server/source/model/players. Open your player files like playerassistant. Player. Playerhandler & search startup or initialize, under the addItem methods you’ll see openInterface("###, 0); remove just this line. Compile & run your server.

You can edit it however you want. But this way will only remove the interface, if you just want to add your server name, using a photo editing software & open the file, you can find it in your cache located in your c:/ drive.

I’m not on my computer so I’m not sure which .java file it’s in, but you’ll find it if you do as I said.

Read full topic
